<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - FUEL INJECTION PUMP - Priming Fuel Injection System
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Priming Fuel Injection System</title>
        <para>After replacing fuel injection pump or replacing fuel supply lines, prime fuel system using these
            procedures:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the bleed screws at the fuel filter header (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051146">11.46</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) and fuel injection pump (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1051147">11.47</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Operate priming pump until pump action provides solid fuel at the bleed screw. Close the
                screw.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position injection pump shutoff lever in run position with electric shutoff or mechanical
                cable.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Crank engine for fifteen seconds.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Crank engine for no more than 15 second intervals.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Start engine and operate until engine runs smoothly.</para>
            <figure id="ef1051146" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3085" filename="../figeg3/EG3085.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.46.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Fuel Filter Header</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Bleeder Screw</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1051147" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg3086" filename="../figeg3/EG3086.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11.47.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Fuel Injection Pump</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Bleeder Screw</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
